    "The biopsychosocial model posits that health and illness are determined by the dynamic interaction of biological factors (genetics, neurochemistry, medical conditions), psychological factors (thoughts, emotions, behaviors, coping mechanisms), and social factors (relationships, culture, socioeconomic status, environmental stressors). These domains are interconnected—changes in one area inevitably affect the others. The model challenges purely biomedical approaches by recognizing that psychosocial factors significantly influence disease onset, progression, and treatment outcomes.",
