    "Management includes developing a collaborative treatment plan that addresses identified needs across all three domains. Biological interventions may include referrals for medical evaluation or medication management. Psychological interventions include individual therapy, psychoeducation, and skill-building. Social interventions address environmental stressors through case management, resource linkage, advocacy, and community support development. Regular reassessment ensures the plan remains responsive to changing needs.",
