    "Risk assessment integrates actuarial methods (statistical prediction based on identified risk factors) with structured professional judgment (clinician expertise applied within a framework). Risk factors are characteristics associated with increased probability of harm, while protective factors are characteristics that buffer against risk. Dynamic risk factors (changeable, such as substance use or hopelessness) are targeted in intervention, while static risk factors (unchangeable, such as history of attempts) inform overall risk level.",
