    "Cultural formulation examines four key domains: (1) cultural identity of the individual, including ethnic and cultural reference groups, language, and degree of acculturation; (2) cultural conceptualizations of distress, including cultural idioms, perceived causes, and explanatory models; (3) cultural factors related to the psychosocial environment, including social stressors, social support, and cultural norms; and (4) cultural elements of the clinician-client relationship, including differences in culture, language, and social status that may affect the therapeutic alliance.",
